#: ../../manual/data_system/scenes.rst:4
msgid "Scenes"
msgstr "场景--阿尔翻译"

#: ../../manual/data_system/scenes.rst:6
msgid ""
"Scenes are a way to organize your work. Each blend-file can contain "
"multiple scenes which share other data such as objects and materials"
msgstr "Scenes 是个对管理你的项目非常有用的工具。每个 ``.blend`` 文件都包含了多个场景，这些场景可能共享了物体或者材质等数据。"

#: ../../manual/data_system/scenes.rst:9
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Scene management and library appending/linking are based on Blender's "
":doc:`Library and Data System </data_system/index>`, so it is a good idea"
" to read that manual page first if you are not familiar with the basics "
"of that system."
msgstr ""
"场景管理和库的追加和链接是基于Blender的 :doc:`库和数据系统 </data_system/index>` "
"上的。如果你不熟悉这套系统的时候，最好去阅读下相关的手册知识。"

#: ../../manual/data_system/scenes.rst:13
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can select and create scenes with the *Scene selector* in the *Info* "
"editor header (at the top of most Blender screen layouts)."
msgstr "你可用信息窗口菜单栏中的 *场景选择器* 选择和创建场景（信息菜单栏一般在 Blender 界面布局中的顶部）。"

#: ../../manual/data_system/scenes.rst:19
